
to generate HTML report we can do following steps: 
Step 1: Run the JMeter test and save the results
Open Command Prompt or Terminal and navigate to the JMeter bin folder.

cd /path/to/apache-jmeter/bin

Run your test in non-GUI mode:

jmeter -n -t TestPlan.jmx -l results.jtl

Parameters:

-n = Non-GUI mode
-t = Test plan (.jmx)
-l = Result file (.jtl)
Example:

jmeter -n -t D:\JMeter\TestPlan.jmx -l D:\JMeter\Results\results.jtl

Step 2: Generate the HTML Report
After the test completes, run:

jmeter -g results.jtl -o HTMLReport

Or with full paths:

jmeter -g D:\JMeter\Results\results.jtl -o D:\JMeter\Results\HTMLReport

Parameters:

-g = Input JTL file
-o = Output folder for the HTML report
Note: The output folder (HTMLReport) must not already exist, or it must be empty.

Step 3: Open the Report
Go to the output folder and open:

HTMLReport/index.html

in your web browser.

One Command (Run Test + Generate Report)
jmeter -n -t D:\JMeter\TestPlan.jmx -l D:\JMeter\Results\results.jtl
jmeter -g D:\JMeter\Results\results.jtl -o D:\JMeter\Results\HTMLReport

If you get an error
Error:

Cannot write to 'HTMLReport' as folder already exists

Delete the existing report folder or specify a new folder:

rmdir /s /q D:\JMeter\Results\HTMLReport
jmeter -g D:\JMeter\Results\results.jtl -o D:\JMeter\Results\HTMLReport

Example for Windows
cd C:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin

jmeter -n -t C:\Tests\API_Test.jmx -l C:\Tests\Results\results.jtl

jmeter -g C:\Tests\Results\results.jtl -o C:\Tests\Results\HTMLReport

This will generate an HTML dashboard with metrics such as response times, throughput, error percentage, active threads, and response time distribution.



